    • Method Detail

      • seek

        Seeker<KEY,​VALUE> seek​(KEY fromInclusive,
                             KEY toExclusive,
                             PageCursorTracer cursorTracer)
                      throws IOException
        Seeks hits in this tree, given a key range. Hits are iterated over using the returned Seeker. There's no guarantee that neither the Seeker.Factory nor the Seeker.Factory instances are immutable and so if caller wants to cache the results it's safest to copy the instances, or rather their contents, into its own result cache.

        Seeks can go either forwards or backwards depending on the values of the key arguments.

        • A fromInclusive that is smaller than the toExclusive results in results in ascending order.
        • A fromInclusive that is bigger than the toExclusive results in results in descending order.
        Parameters:
        fromInclusive - lower bound of the range to seek (inclusive).
        toExclusive - higher bound of the range to seek (exclusive).
        cursorTracer - underlying page cursor tracer
        Returns:
        a Seeker used to iterate over the hits within the specified key range.
        Throws:
        IOException - on error reading from index.
